---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@/components/container.astro";
import Sectionhead from "@/components/sectionhead.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<Layout title="AI Systems | AnichLabs OÜ">
  <Container>
    <Sectionhead>
      <Fragment slot="title">AI Systems</Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="desc">Clinical AI strategy, AI agents, and automation, built EU-sovereign and audit-ready.</Fragment>
    </Sectionhead>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl mt-16">
      <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-lg">
        Most clinical AI products solve the wrong problem, or solve the right problem wrong. Health-tech teams have the engineering skills to build sophisticated AI systems, but without clinicians embedded in requirements, products miss the workflow, ignore the regulatory shape of the use case, or generate outputs that nobody trusts.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-lg mt-4">
        AnichLabs OÜ designs and builds AI systems that operate under real regulatory constraints. Our work spans clinical decision support, AI agents for operational workflows, and automation pipelines that run on EU-sovereign infrastructure with full audit trails. Led by a medical doctor and computer scientist, we translate clinical needs into technically sound and regulatorily compliant AI products.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">What we deliver</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <Icon name="uil:notes" class="w-7 h-7 mb-3" style="color: #003399" />
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Clinical AI Strategy</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Use case definition, product requirements, and regulatory alignment, before you build.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <Icon name="uil:robot" class="w-7 h-7 mb-3" style="color: #003399" />
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">AI Agents and Automation</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Event-driven systems with role-routed prompts, RAG, and human oversight.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <Icon name="uil:server" class="w-7 h-7 mb-3" style="color: #003399" />
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">EU-Sovereign Deployment</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">CPU-only inference, EU hosting, no US providers, GDPR and EU AI Act ready by design.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <Icon name="uil:user-md" class="w-7 h-7 mb-3" style="color: #003399" />
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Ongoing Clinical Advisory</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Available throughout development to review outputs, advise on validation, and support regulatory submissions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">Common questions</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <details class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 rounded-xl p-5 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-gray-800 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center text-sm">
            How is this different from a clinical advisor?
            <Icon name="uil:angle-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" />
          </summary>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mt-3">Clinical advisors provide domain knowledge. We translate that knowledge into technical requirements, regulatory documentation, and product decisions, which is a different and rarer skill set.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 rounded-xl p-5 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-gray-800 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center text-sm">
            At what stage should we engage?
            <Icon name="uil:angle-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" />
          </summary>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mt-3">As early as possible. Clinical and regulatory decisions made before the first line of code save months of rework later. We also work with teams reviewing existing products.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 rounded-xl p-5 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-gray-800 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center text-sm">
            Can this be combined with regulatory compliance work?
            <Icon name="uil:angle-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" />
          </summary>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mt-3">Yes. Clinical strategy and EU AI Act/MDR compliance are tightly linked. We often deliver them as a combined engagement so your product is clinically and regulatorily aligned from day one.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl mt-16 mb-10 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">Building intelligent systems for healthcare?</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 mt-3">Book a free 30-minute call to discuss your project.</p>
      <a href="https://calendly.com/chris-anichlabs/30min" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
        class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors"
        style="background-color: #003399">
        <Icon name="uil:calendar-alt" class="w-5 h-5" />
        Book a Free Call
      </a>
    </div>

  </Container>
</Layout>